reviews.text: Beautiful home with a great staff that wants to help make the most of your visit. Enjoyed a self-tour but unable to get in on the guided one. The guided one was already full so get there early so you don't miss out on the library and 2nd floor. We will have to go back.

My school age son and I went there the other day. Our tour guide was Sheila and she was amazing. She had so many details and tailored the tour to fit both my son and I (like stories about the boys who lived in the house. My son is still talking about them riding motorcycles through the front and back doors). We also got to see things you don’t get to see in the self guided tour. This was a great experience for us and I would recommend a visit to anyone!

I've always adore this place since I was a child and my mother would take me. Fun half day activity for children 12 and up. Great little piece of history to partake in. Always great to go back for a visit. I recommend always looking at the website for time and date information though, because they do events that may interfere with regular business hours. If your ever in Des monies I highly recommend.
It's a nice way to spend an afternoon... Wish more of the house was accessible to the public however...

I had my wedding and reception at the Salisbury House. I enjoyed every bit of our time there!!! They were organized and adjusted to the needs of the day that arose! I could not suggest a better place!!! They are extremely kind people!
Great experience. The whole museum is quiet and beautiful, feel peace inside it.

Such an underrated place.

Showcases popular artists like Pablo Picasso, John Singer Sargent, Edward Hopper, Georgia O'Keeffe, Grant Wood.

Admission has been free recently. The gift shop is one of my favorite places for gifts in Iowa. Please come here if you haven't already.

Everyone here is nice and social.

Get there when they've got an interesting collection, they need a better mix of pieces and sculptures. Good learning resource if you're taking a class, wish they had more places to sit & sketch. Standing & drawing takes a lot of stamina & gets hard on the back.
Amazing place, that not a lot of people, even the residents of Des Moines, think about.  Incredible collection considering the size with works from many renown artists.
World-class art in a small Midwestern city. Good stuff!

I feel bad posting a negative review, but feel like this place isn’t being run as well as it could be. 

1) The exhibits never change. There is a Lego one there that really isn’t that great and has been there about a year. If it’s a money issue, do some fundraising!

2) They have poor rules about where they can do activities. For instance now they have this giant, kind of creepy doll name Stuffie and you have to go into a dark and lifeless theatre with no music or anything kid friendly about it. No one really goes to it, but if they had it out in the open area it would surely attract more kids and might have a chance of being fun.

3) Their snow closures. We drove into town one day to find a sign in the door that they were closed due to snow. No schools were closed, the public library was open...it just felt likesort of lazy and really frustrating as a member. 

4) The upkeep of the building. I am going to attempt to post a picture, but some stuff is really looking run down and could use a fresh coat of paint at least.

I don’t know who runs the place, or who is on the board, but I think they could all be doing a better job to stop the decline of this place.

I bought a membership 2018  I  and my children enjoyed during a school  outing in December 2017. The dinosaur  display  was on way to long the lego display  was not exciting to older children and adults its still there since  last September  2018  the theaters  were closed for remodeling  2 months in late summer  and early fall  2018 was a very boring place that  i will not buy another  membership. Once you get a lot of memberships you close things to remodel so sad no ever good recommendation  for your place just over  priced food.
I like the place it gives me and my boyfriend a fun time to reminisce on our childhood but I just wish it didn’t close so early so we could actually spend the whole day after work and school is done.

As a father of infinitely curious children, this place was an endless fascination for them. A real wonderland for them. Will return the next time we are in Des Moines as there is yet much to be explored.

We love visiting the science center--the I max theater is the reason for 3 stars. We saw transformers in IMAX at the science center like 8 years ago and I had forgotten about the horrible film conversion until reading these reviews. When we saw Transformers, it was very obvious that they projected regular format--not imax--onto the dome. I know this because there's a scene where a helicopter is descending straight vertical but the projection skews it so much it's dizzying to watch. I hope they fix the issues with the IMAX theater. It has great potential but not worth vomiting over.

We like going here all year. In the winter it's nice to go somewhere that is warm and peaceful. My daughter (2) loves going around and looking at all the different plants and flowers. In the summer their outdoor area is absolutely stunning. We love seeing the waterfalls (indoor and outdoor). Its a terrific learning experience. The staff is very friendly as well.

This is easily my favorite place in Des Moines. It is so peaceful and tranquil being surrounded by the large varieties of plants. My children love the koi ponds. The restaurant located within is also delightful. My family LOVE every visit that we have made to the Greater Des Moines Botanical Garden. You will always find something new!!
Great place to go to get out of the winter and get into some green! $10 for nonmember admission so grab a book and hang out or grab a camera. Great spot for a photo shoot. Usually fairly busy.

I went to this place in the middle of winter, so we didn't get to see the outside of the venue. However the inside was open and we took our time when walking around. We were really impressed with how everything was put together and how much there was to see...i would definitely consider going here again in the future, since the inside was so impressive, I'd imagine the outside is just as good, if not better.

Though it was a bit crowded due to a Blues Concert the last time I went, I still enjoyed my time there.
It's such a beautiful, serene place. I can easily go there after a hectic day and regain my peace of mind...
This place has the best chocolate shakes and chicken sandwiches in the city of Des Moines. I highly recommend this place.
Best burgers ever. Never had a zombie burger never want to. B-Bops IS THE BOMB!!!

The food is good WHEN ITS MADE CORRECTLY. Yesterday my co worker went and was accused of using counterfeit money when it was straight from the atm @ Verdian bank. They didn't want to return it either for "evidence" his bank teller told him the employees just wanted to keep the $20 and were using the marker too heavily causing the mark to darken instead of being light. This store is the worst. The staff don't listen, i always say no pickle and yet theres always pickles. Even if its on the receipt! you will get interrupted while ordering or asked multiple times to repeat it. Even if you speak loudly and clear for some reason orders are always messed up. Go to the one on Fleur instead! The manager accused my co worker when really the idiot doesnt know how to use a marker once instead of drowing the bill in marker fluid. on top of all this the food order was still wrong! This staff needs better training and a better manager.
Delicious food and the best chocolate shakes ever. Only bad thing-it's in Iowa and we live in MI
Always great. Fast and efficient!

Absolutely scrumptious pastries. I am a fiend for coffee and a sweet treat to start of my morning. I came here multiple mornings throughout our visit to Des Moines.

Their pecan scones were phenomenal. I even got a loaf of their sprouted sourdough bread for the ride. Amazing place.

I had been staying up the street at a local establishment and decided to forego the boring, greasy, continental breakfast. After scouring reviews for eateries in walking distance? Decided to try Scenic Route Bakery and am extremely happy that I did! 
If ever you should find yourself in Des Moines? Wherever you might be lodging. Scenic Route is worth it. The pastries were wonderful and the house blend coffee I chose? The Honey Bee was perfect for my palate. I'd be hard pressed to have any desire to stop anywhere else when I'm back in Des Moines again.

Cheers!

I cannot say enough good things about this place!!! I was looking for a lesser-known, cute cafe to settle in and read my book while I sipped a hot drink. Scenic Route Bakery was everything I hoped for and MORE! Nice selection of pastries, plus some light lunch fare (get the chicken salad - it is ginormous and oh-so-delicious!). And the place is huge! It was constantly busy but I never felt crowded. It was cozy yet modern. They had something for everyone. I WILL be back! This is my new "spot" to get away from it all.
Delicious pastries and coffee. Great spot for meeting a friend to catch up or a casual business meeting. Friendly staff and great location.
The best croissants in town. Perfectly flakey and buttery.
This place gave me PTSD and I’m glad it’s shut down.

Service, food, and clean woman's bathroom all need help. Came on Saturday April 16th, seemed that both girls at the counter were more interested in a guy then doing their job. I noticed that the "cooks" did not have hair nets or anything but long hair. The fries taste store bought, and the spicy itallian sandwich was okay. The chicken sandwich is salty and horrible. Won't be back anytime soon. My wife went to use the bathroom and she came back and told me it was disgusting.

My family has been going here years. It use to be something to rave about. Tonight I had the worst experience!! The service at the counter was horrible. The bartender had to be drunk he was so rude & sarcastic! He shouldn't even be working in the service  No servers came around to see if the was anything else needed. I will not go there again!!
Love the pizza and the bbq. Make sure you get sugar biscuits!!! They are awesome.
A group of us drove thru Des Moines from Minneapolis to Omaha only to find out to were closed. Please post on web site when your closed!! It says now your open...
Great place for a quick bite! Food is always hot an fresh! Love their hot sauce! Been coming here to the new place and the old place which was like 30 feet away for like 30 years now!

Food was good overall. Menu had many options. Tacos were topped with cheese and lettuce. A bit Americanized. Would love to some more authentic options such as cilantro, peppers, and lime. The steak flour taco is solid!
Hometown favorite. If you grew up in Des Moines, you've eaten at tasty tacos. They gave a taco for whatever your craving. Original taco is my steady eddy. Great job guys. Thank you

This THE spot for Mexican food in Des Moines. Pretty well know out of the state as well. Whether you're passing through or a native you owe it to yourself to visit at least once for traditional Mexican food at a solid price.
i dont care how much diarrhea i get after eating here. these tacos are worth going out and buying new underwear every week or so.  id rate 10/10 if i could. keep up the great work guys.

Waveland Cafe is riding the crest of public approval these days and for good reasons! Good food, friendly service, hometown character and history.  My only complaint about the "skillet" meal was that it looked and tasted like an omelet over hash browns. Where's the skillet? Parking is a hassle even if you get a space out front - then it's hard to get out. Even so it was a full cafe at 10 am on Tuesday.

Food was very good, could tell they care about what they put on the table, and I appreciate that they used butter on the toast. Seems small, but I HATE the taste of margarine.
We were a little miffed when one person in a party of 6 was able to sit when our party of seven was there, ready to go, but the person was there before us so I suppose it's fair.

Pricing is good. Staff is friendly, and they work quickly. Worth a short wait, but I'm not certain that I'd hang if the line happened to be out the door.
Delicious! Everything I've gotten here has been delicious. Coffee lacks in flavor big time! I would recommend this place.
Waveland is always great! The blueberry pancakes are top notch. Service is excellent. My Eggs Benedict special was perfect. 5 stars!!!!
Keep your place in line, the wait for a table goes quick. try the everything hash browns. So good!

I'm reminded of the old Johnny's Vets Club in historic Valley Junction; this cozy old restaurant is the last of a dying breed of classy, Italian-American joints. The food is awesome, Service is impeccable, and prices are just right. I just found my new favorite restaurant.
An old-school Des Moines eatery. Chucks isn't fancy, but the service and food are great.  I really recommend the Italian fried chicken dinner.
Steak deboro was wonderful. Wait staff was very good. Very nice evening
The pizza and the onions were amazing! The waitress was not very attentive! Loved the atmosphere and the food! I will definitely return! I loved the thin crust!

Giving it 3 stars cause the service is unsurpassed. Had cavetelli...was disappointed...expected fullbodied marinara instead it was some spicy hot sweet combo and watery. Needed more reduction. When I order Italian want it to taste Italian...not some new twist you'd expect from Asian cuisine. Friends pizza was great...and service was outstanding.

Found out about this place on a TV show. So I had to drive to Des Moines to check it out. The two parking lots and the street parking were full. When we pulled up to the Restaurant. We were seated after a short wait at the front part of the place next to the kitchen. The food be cooked smelled Great. We were seated at a large table and the five of us all order different meals. Each Meal came with one or two sides. I had Blacken catfish. My family had Chicken, Ribs and brisket sandwich's. Sides of baked apples, collard Greens. Are server was the greatest and the rest of the staff were excellent.
This is one of our "go to" places. Never disappointed. Expect a wait but always worth it. You'll be happy with anything on the menu, but the brisket and the ribs are a must.

Awesome food. I had the sampler platter where you pick 3 meats and two sides. The ribs were pretty good. They do kinda char them on the outside which looks worse than it tastes. It actually tastes pretty good. The chicken was fairly good and the brisket...yeah the brisket is where it's at! By far the best out of the 3 meats! Very juicy and delicious! I very much highly recommend getting the brisket! The beans and rice was ok. I'm not a huge fan of beans and rice anyway but I did eat it all so it was alright but the horseradish mashed potatoes were also amazing! They weren't overpowered with horseradish and had just the right amount of kick to them. Overall I would totally go back for the brisket and the horseradish mashed potatoes for sure! I've heard the duck is really good there and wouldn't mind trying that sometime yet too.

Haven't done a review for some time yet had to get this out to you all after eating here last night. Forgot how much I enjoy this place, the menu, and staff. Offered drinks upon arrival and ended up ordering a bottle of Merlot off the their end-of-bin list. Nice. Were seated after talking with the owner, Mike. He recommended the Catfish Cakes. We ordered them, the Shrimp and Grits, and Chicken Pasta. Nailed it. The Catfish cakes rocked. Get them! The rest of the food was finished today as Daytona 500 left-overs.

Ordered the 24 hour brisket, sauteed vegetables and braised collard greens. Brisket could be cut with my fork and had a beautiful bark on it. Sauteed vegetables we're a medley of brussel sprouts, snap peas, bell pepper and onions, quite tasty. The greens...if you enjoy collard greens, get them as long as you're good with pork. Waitress was friendly, prompt and attentive. 

TL:DR, I'll be going back as soon as I can stand up again from the massive portion of food
Fantastic food! The owner came by and checked on us. The menus have a bio about him. Good drink menu. My wife is surf, and I am turf. Fantastic options for either palate.

My wife and I went on a dinner date to miyabi 9 and had a wonderful time. we were well taken care of in all aspects of our service with some complimentary service being that it was our first time and we were blown away at the quality and craftsmanship that they put into their sushi as well as their desserts. The restaurant itself is quaint and very cozy and clean. we ate at the bar which we don't typically do but really enjoyed it watching and communicating with the chefs.  We will most certainly be heading back there in the near future because we left so satisfied. We would highly recommend Miyabi 9 for sushi over the many other options in the metro area.

The waiter remembered us from our last visit, in June of last year, and remembered our order. That is the kind of excellent service we get at Miyabi. The sushi is great, and the owner is sweet and kind. We love this place.

Probably the best sushi restaurant I've found in Des Moines. It's unique but fits in well with the area. Very friendly and very cozy, willing to walk you through the best way to eat the specials. The prices aren't bad at all, especially for the quality of meal. My boyfriend and I treated ourselves to a nice lunch with drinks for around $50. It was so good I didn't even feet a chance to take a picture because our food was gone so fast.
Excellent food & service!  The prices are on target.  I highly recommend the lunch box meals.

Paradise Pizza is a spot you drive by and never remember to stop in to. But boy is it worth it! They have daily lunch buffets with fresh salad, fresh bread, home made soup, home made pastas, and a good selection of pizza. Their pasta specials are rave worthy also - unique recipes with very fresh ingredients... and they come with that fresh baked bread. Highly recommend this place!
Best BBQ I have had in a long time. Brisket and ribs are amazing! Cozy neighborhood feel to a great little restaurant. Totally recommend this BBQ joint.

Awesome food and Awesome service!!! Very friendly and helpful staff. Very generous portions and the prices are very fair!
The meats are moist, tender and very flavorful. And the baked beans are the best I've ever had!!!
If you haven't already tried them out, I highly recommend you do!
Another one of Des Moines hidden treasures.  Very good BBQ, seating space is limited though.  Be prepared to eat outside or order to go
The meats are the stars here, they are rich, flavorful and smoky. The sides were a mixed bag. I liked the meaty baked beans, but the cole slaw was drenched in dressing.
The meats are so good. I tried the "spicy barbeque sauce" and it was molasses-y, and not too spicy. There is a great selection of sides. Fresh hot cornbread adds a homey touch.

Small but fabulous bistro/restaurant. My wife and I had the four course chef's tasting menu and it was absolutely delightful. Staff was super friendly and explained everything we needed to know about the menu and the food that was delivered. We each had a cocktail and both were also very good. Dress is smart casual my wife had a nice blouse and dark jeans, I was wearing slacks and a button shirt but we saw more casual and more business dress there as well. Before we left we were already planning a return with friends. Prices were reasonable for the quality and taste of the food. I believe the 4 course tasting menu without wine pairings was $65. They also have a 6 course tasting menu that was more. Most menu items ranged from $10 (sides) to $66 (filet) with most entrees being in the $30 range with outliers that were cheaper and more expensive. All in all, very good food especially for the price. My wife and I couldn't think of anyplace we had been on our travels that matched the quality at this price point from New York to Maui. Give it a try you won't regret it.

Very nice ambiance. First two courses were very good, especially the seafood.  Generous pours of house wine.  Bread was overdone. Not enough servers led to spotty service.  Prices were reasonable given the quality.  Worth another visit.

the food was really good but I don't think the waitress could have hated me anymore. There were four of us at the table and none of us knew what I possibly did to to deserve the way she was treating me, the way she spoke to everyone else the table was completely different from how she spoke to and treated me. Definitely Maybe experience not as pleasant as it could have been but luckily I had good company so we were just laughing about it. Food was phenomenal and the hostess and bartender were very friendly and nice.
This restaurant has great chef inspired food, wonderful service and an intimate atmosphere. It is wonderful for a fancy date night.

Delicious! 3 course dinner menu is $53 and changes seasonally. The Chef is from France, and the food is meticulously good. The egg appetizer was amazing, with all the flavors on point and the egg cooked perfectly. 

The service is professional, the atmosphere is nice, and it’s a perfect place for an evening out or for something special.

I was there on a wedding day and this gentleman actually stole my jacket. So I was able to get in touch with the GM Katy S. Without any trouble at all she was on it looked at the video and had my very wonderful jacket back in less then a day. Thanks also great spot for any situation really the place is big enough to have a company party and still have enough room for the public to be able to come in and play pool shuffle board

OK so I hate to say it but it's your run of the mill after work happy hour. I've been there twice both times it was either crowded or not very many people there. On the night we went where the crowd was bustling they only had 3 bartenders total for 2 different bars. Very difficult to get drinks. But cool if you're just gonna pop in for a few min. Oh & outdated decor.

I visited strictly to watch a game during happy hour. I was quite impressed. Very good and attentive customer service, and outstanding prices on some draft beers, considering the area. $3 for selected drafts is a downright steal in this part of Arlington.
Service, food, pool tables. Bring your own cue. Good specials. A little crowded for real shooters after 5.
Cool spot to hang out and play some games with friends. Good food, cheap drinks, and lots of games. They have pool, ping pong, arcade games, board games, darts.  Lots of fun here!

A great find in downtown Des Moines Escargot, Onion Soup, Sandwiches, Fresh Seafood, Full Dinner Menu what more can you ask for. The servers are very helpful explaining any questions you may have with a knowledgeable answer. The ambiance is most pleasant and no rushing. The prices are quite reasonable for the quality of food served. We had a great meal here when in town for a conference. It was a Monday night and got really busy, which affected the service. Our waiter acknowledged and apologized. We were not in a hurry and fine with it, but I could tell other diners were not as patient.

We've eaten at Django quite often, but at the former location. This new location we will be visiting very soon. No matter, whenever you can choose a restaurant, not matter which special occasion it is or no matter which special guest is in town, it says a lot about the quality of food and service. And that is Django's. It is exceptional in every way. The food is superior because they pay attention to the details. We have dined at Django's as a couple, with family, with friends and for business reasons. I have never had a bad experience or chosen a dish I thought was of lesser quality than the previous times. Drinks are cold and well made. The wine is also for fine dining.

Alexa was a great waitress. Someone in our party couldn't have alcohol in their food and she went above and beyond to make sure it didn't. The food was excellent. The Scallops are great. We will be going back.

The wine selection was good. Service was okay at best-at most points in the evening we’d have empty, used dishes stacked up on the edge of the table and our server couldn’t catch the hint that maybe they should be cleared. Even when he did clear some he’d only take one or two. The Brussels were tasty but salted poorly because some spots were like a salt lick and others were just right. You really can’t screw up French fries too badly so those were good. I ordered a steak salad and I’d say it was disappointing. I expected it to have more developed flavors, instead I got lettuce, cold veggies, an unseasoned steak and tons of dressing. I’d go back for cocktail hour only next time.
Wow, was super awesome. Little expensive but very worth it. Staff was great, food was superb and very relaxed environment.
The meatballs are big and tasty.  Pasta trio was excellent. Service was good, waiter refilled our drinks frequently. Dessert was very good. We took home enough leftovers to provide lunch.

A great place. Food is fantastic!
Tara, our server, was friendly and very efficient. We enjoyed every minute we were at Tursi's Latin King. Thank you for being the best in Des Moines. 💕
First time dining at Latin King. Excellent variety of food and very well prepared. Our waitress was extremely friendly and helpful. We will definitely be back!

Not impressed. Heard good reviews so I wanted to try it. The shrimp in my pasta were overcooked. Bread was cold and salad was ordinary.  Too pricey for the food.  I'd rather go to Olive Garden. Server was friendly tho!

Our second time visiting Latin King provided a much better experience.  The facility is beautifully decorated for Christmas.  Our waiter was efficient and pleasant.  Our appetizers were delicious.  Although the entree platters of food looked inviting, but there wasn't a lot of flavor or taste (Chicken Marsala and Chicken Spiedini).

Wonderful people, helpful & polite. This is a clean, bright & pleasant store.... Just walking in raised my spirits & I bought several impulse buys after the meat Dept. helpfully matched a competitor's ad I had brought. And I always appreciate the courtesy of assistance to my car. Thank you & Well done !!!!!
Fast check out.  Carry most essential items. In and out in no time.  Staff are reachable.  Price is reasonable.
Been a customer since they opened & never looked back. Have everything I need and a great meat counter.
Great place to shop.simple and has good prices. They all take you out to your car
We've moved our shopping to Fairway from HyVee. Friendlier people and great product
